===Etymology===
Borrowed from {{bor|en|es|barbacoa}} (whence also {{m|en|barbecue}}), from {{der|en|tnq|barbakoa||framework of sticks}}, the raised wooden structure the natives used to either sleep on or cure meat. Originally “meal of roasted meat or fish”.

